{
  "text": "Matrilysins (MMP-7 and MMP-26) belong to the smallest members of MMPs and do not contain the hemopexinlike domain. For MMP-23 the hydrophobic N-terminal signal anchor is specific [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . MMP-19, MMP-20, MMP-27 and MMP-12 are considered to be the first members of a new MMPs group . Structures of other domains of matrilysins are similar to other MMPs, i.e. a signal sequence, the latent domain, catalytic domain and C-terminal propeptide-like hemopexin, but lack structures specific for other groups [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Some MMPs, such as MT-MMPs and stromelysin-3, contain protein convertase specific recognition motifs (Arg-X-Arg-X-Lys-Arg, where X represents any amino acid) [CITATION_5] .",
